                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that the application of the new tariff immediately after
                    signing the protocol, only exempting goods in transit, is favored by a majority
                    of the diplomatic corps. In view of the abolition of the free list, he has
                    raised an objection, suggesting a delay of three months.</p>
                <p>Instructions requested.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
